<br>
The person that was arguing with me was a monk, who quoted his own damage bonuses as being constant until delay 40, then being another constant from delay 40+.  Since I don't doubt what he read from his weapons, I have to assume that monks have a different table.  Likely rogues are on a different table too.  (In his case, he was insisting that it was like that for every class.  Hence my desire for a better table.)<br>
<br>
However, you are correct in that (I assume) warriors, shadow knights, and paladins all get the same damage bonuses.  Probably rangers and bards do as well (can they use 2 handed weapons?). <p><center>
